A teenager at a school in Finland went on the rampage Wednesday, shooting dead seven classmates and the headmistress, having first signalled his intentions in a video posted on the YouTube Internet site.
The American-style shooting sent shockwaves through Finland, where such violence is extremely rare.
Eight people were killed,
Pekka-Eric Auvinen, an 18-year-old student known to support radical causes, carried out his massacre at the Jokela High School in southern Finland on Wednesday, shooting dead three women, including the headmistress and a nurse, aged 25, 42 and 61, and five boys aged between 16 and 18, police said.
